      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0007">
               <p>A native of the district of <placeName>Fahan</placeName> (just outside
                     <placeName>Londonderry</placeName>), Abraham took his <seg ana="degree"
                     >BA</seg> at <placeName>Trinity College, Dublin</placeName> in <date
                     when="1768">1768</date>, was ordained, and served as a curate in the Templemore
                  parish of Londonderry and chaplain at the Chapel (of Ease) of the Immaculate
                  Conception in <placeName>Fahan</placeName>. In <date when="1776">1776</date> he
                  was converted under the influence of Rev. <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers1903.xml"/>Edward Smyth</persName>, and joined
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1903.xml"/>Smyth</persName> for a while
                  preaching in <placeName>Dublin</placeName>. In <date when="1778">1778</date>, at
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s request,
                  Abraham left <placeName>Ireland</placeName> to assist at the new Chapel on
                     <placeName>City Road</placeName> in <placeName>London</placeName> (see his only
                  appearance in the <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi> that year, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Works</hi>, 10:475). He proved physically and temperamentally unsuited to this
                  role and returned to <placeName>Ireland</placeName> the following year. In <date
                     when="1782">1782</date> he was again in <placeName>London</placeName>. The last
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> knew of him,
                  Abraham was confined in a hospital as &apos;insane&apos;. See J. B. Leslie, <hi
                     rend="italic">Derry Clergy</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Parishes</hi>
                  (Enniskillen: Ritchie, <date when="1937">1937</date>), 291; Crookshank, <hi
                     rend="italic">Ireland</hi>, 1:276, 307, 397, 332; and <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> to <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers1235.xml"/>Alexander Knox</persName>, <date
                     when="1778-12-20">Dec. 20, 1778</date> &amp; <date when="1784-02-07">Feb. 7,
                     1784</date>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
